{
  "text": "Besides osteoporotic vertebral bone, it must be recognized that sarcopenia of the trunk muscles leads to dysfunction and affects clinical outcomes, including postoperative rehabilitation [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . However, the contribution of age to decreases in trunk muscle strength is unclear, as reference data in young adults, as well as changes associated with age, have not been investigated in large cohort studies using validated instruments.",
